# »-`-,-

This is the README for `radroots` core libraries, which together constitute a
composable architecture for coordinating local agricultural networks.

## Getting Rad Roots

The preferred method to download `radroots` source code is to use git.

To download `radroots` do the following:

    git clone https://radroots.dev/git/lib.git

If you have questions about `radroots` or if you wish to be notified of releases,
you can browse and/or join the `radroots` mailing list:

    https://radroots.dev/lists/listinfo

Rad Roots is built on Love for the Planet and its People.

